Note:
JSX/TSX to HIR Translation Test Suite

Total Tests: 12
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/jsx/jsx_to_hir.runa" as Translator
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

@Reasoning:
Counter triple shared across the JSX-to-HIR driver. Same layout as peer
suites for unified-runner compatibility.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
total at offset 0, passed at 8, failed at 16; mutated via raw
Layout.memory_set_int64 because results is shared by handle.
@End Implementation

Type called "TestResults":
    total as Integer
    passed as Integer
    failed as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Top-level driver for JSX-to-HIR translation. Calls 12 named test
processes covering the JSX surface (element, fragment, attributes,
children, embedded expression, nested components, member-expression
component, conditional expression) plus four pure-JS constructs
(variable decl, function decl, arrow function, array expression) to
prove the translator handles both inside-JSX and outside-JSX code
paths.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Allocate TestResults, print banner, run all 12 test_* procs against
the shared results buffer, print summary, return 1 if any test failed
else 0.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- All 12 named scenarios translate to non-null HIR -> exit 0
- Any single test_* returns 0 -> results.failed >= 1 -> exit 1
@End TestCases

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be a value of type TestResults with total as 0, passed as 0, failed as 0

    proc print_header

    proc test_simple_jsx from results
    proc test_jsx_fragment from results
    proc test_jsx_attributes from results
    proc test_jsx_children from results
    proc test_jsx_expression from results
    proc test_nested_jsx from results
    proc test_member_expression from results
    proc test_variable_declaration from results
    proc test_function_declaration from results
    proc test_arrow_function from results
    proc test_conditional_expression from results
    proc test_array_expression from results

    proc print_results from results

    If results.failed is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Baseline: a single JSX element with text content. If this doesn't
translate, no later JSX test will work, so this test is intentionally
first.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div>Hello</div>", get its length, call
translate_jsx_to_hir(source, length). Non-null -> [PASS]+passed; null
-> [FAIL]+failed. Frees source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div>Hello</div>" -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Translator returns 0 -> "Simple JSX element: failed", failed += 1
@End TestCases

Process called "test_simple_jsx" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be proc create_string from StringCore with "<div>Hello</div>"
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let hir be proc translate_jsx_to_hir from Translator with source, length

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "Simple JSX element"
        proc deallocate from Layout with source
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "Simple JSX element: failed"
    proc deallocate from Layout with source
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies JSX fragment syntax (<>...</>) — the React-specific shorthand
for grouping siblings without an explicit wrapper element. The
unique <> and </> tokens must be recognized by the lexer.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<><div>A</div><div>B</div></>". Translator
with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source on both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<><div>A</div><div>B</div></>" -> non-null HIR, passed += 1
- Lexer treats <> as < + > separately -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
- Translator drops one of the children -> may still succeed but
  semantics wrong
@End TestCases

Process called "test_jsx_fragment" takes results as Integer returns Integer:
    Let _rtot1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 0, _rtot1 plus 1

    Let source be proc create_string from StringCore with "<><div>A</div><div>B</div></>"
    Let length be proc string_length from StringCore with source
    Let hir be proc translate_jsx_to_hir from Translator with source, length

    If hir is not equal to 0:
        proc print_test_success with "JSX fragment"
        proc deallocate from Layout with source
        Let _rpas1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 8, _rpas1 plus 1
        Return 1
    End If

    proc print_test_failure with "JSX fragment: failed"
    proc deallocate from Layout with source
    Let _rfal1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with results, 16
    proc memory_set_int64 from Layout with results, 16, _rfal1 plus 1

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Verifies JSX attribute parsing with two attributes on a self-closing
input. Catches a regression where the attribute loop exits after one
attribute, which would silently lose props.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build `<input type="text" placeholder="Name" />`.
Translator with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source on
both paths.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input with two attributes -> non-null HIR carrying both, passed += 1
- Translator drops second attribute and fails -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

