@Reasoning:
Verifies multiple sibling children at the same depth. A child-loop
exit-after-first regression would silently truncate the second
<p>Text</p> sibling.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div><h1>Title</h1><p>Text</p></div>".
Translator with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input with two sibling children -> non-null HIR with both children,
  passed += 1
- Translator drops second sibling -> may still succeed (silent
  corruption) or returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

