@Reasoning:
Verifies JSX-embedded expression with {curly} braces. This is the
boundary where the JSX lexer must hand off to the JS expression parser
and then resume JSX lexing after the closing }.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div>{name}</div>". Translator with explicit
length. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div>{name}</div>" -> non-null HIR with embedded identifier
  expression, passed += 1
- Lexer fails to switch mode at { -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
- Lexer fails to switch back to JSX after } -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

