@Reasoning:
Verifies a user-defined component (uppercase tag name) nested inside
a host element. The capital-first-letter convention is what
distinguishes <Component> from <div> in the JSX grammar.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "<div><Component /></div>". Translator with
explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div><Component /></div>" -> non-null HIR with the inner
  node tagged as a user component (not a host element), passed += 1
- Translator treats "Component" as a host tag -> may still succeed
  but semantics wrong; if it returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

