@Reasoning:
Verifies a function declaration that returns JSX. Exercises the
function/JSX boundary: the parser must enter JS function-body mode
on `{`, then transition into JSX mode when it encounters `<` at the
return statement.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "function greet() { return <div>Hi</div>; }".
Translator with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "function greet() { return <div>Hi</div>; }" -> non-null HIR
  with FunctionDecl containing JSX return, passed += 1
- Parser fails to enter JSX mode on `<` -> translator returns 0
  -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

