@Reasoning:
Verifies arrow function with JSX body via `=>`. Catches a regression
where the parser doesn't recognize that `=>` followed by `<` enters
JSX mode rather than starting a TypeScript generic.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build "const App = () => <div>App</div>;". Translator
with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0; free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "const App = () => <div>App</div>;" -> non-null HIR with
  ArrowFunction returning JSX, passed += 1
- Parser misreads `<` after `=>` as a comparison -> translator returns
  0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

