@Reasoning:
Verifies the JSX-embedded ternary (`isActive ? <span> : <span>`).
This is a common React pattern for conditional rendering and stresses
the mode switching between JSX and JS expression contexts twice
within a single set of curly braces.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Increment total. Build the conditional ternary expression containing
two JSX branches. Translator with explicit length. Branch on hir != 0;
free source.
@End Implementation

@TestCases:
- Input "<div>{isActive ? <span>Yes</span> : <span>No</span>}</div>"
  -> non-null HIR with ternary containing two JSX nodes, passed += 1
- Parser fails to re-enter JSX mode after `?` -> translator returns 0
  -> failed += 1
- Parser conflates `:` of ternary with JSX namespaced attribute
  -> translator returns 0 -> failed += 1
@End TestCases

